qkHz0qHBEsJBpn0jVGgpGlporSvWOPcyv6XN2X5fa1XPO\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying task transitions**\\n\\nI need to ensure I'm using active_task_cli to show the verify state and advance through all transitions. Since there's a priority change, I should overwrite ACTIVE_TASK.md before I do any substantial work. It might help to use a full-file write to rebuild the file, then read it back. The instructions say to overwrite it clearly when priority changes. I'll check out the script and the template to make sure everything aligns well.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JObCHgJhlk1hJWopZ0Bi35Dv|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b28819b9fbfd4c067425859","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"~/.openclaw/skills/openclaw-workspace/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"~/.openclaw/skills/openclaw-workspace/SKILL.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_EfQBcK6OOyN0te5KXiOBNviW|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b38819ba5da9f9323421bc2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK_TEMPLATE.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK_TEMPLATE.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3wfhLNQZtUT0xOyn1q6ViWKI|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b40819ba3ddf8a1ba8786bc","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/active_task_cli.py"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/active_task_cli.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_G6FMAWPQUGDij311QbztY6Xh|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b44819baacce7e1e243a6f6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/active_task_cli.py show --path /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":60},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/active_task_cli.py show --path /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\",\"timeout\":60}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":157,"output":532,"cacheRead":95232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95921,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774498315329,"responseId":"resp_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b20e3cc0819b811ed00f5571937e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"66179edb","parentId":"595f237d","timestamp":"2026-03-26T04:12:11.829Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JObCHgJhlk1hJWopZ0Bi35Dv|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b28819b9fbfd4c067425859","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: openclaw-workspace\ndescription: Use when maintaining or optimizing OpenClaw workspace files — AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, SOUL.md, USER.md, IDENTITY.md, HEARTBEAT.md, BOOT.md, MEMORY.md, and related checklists and memory files. Covers workspace auditing, token budget analysis, new agent workspace setup from scratch, memory distillation, and cross-file consistency reviews.\n---\n\n# OpenClaw Workspace Skill\n\n## Overview\n\nOpenClaw workspace files form the agent's \"soul and memory\" — they are injected into the system prompt on every turn (or on relevant turns), giving the agent its identity, behavioral rules, environmental knowledge, and long-term memory. Managing these files well is critical: bloat wastes tokens, redundancy creates confusion, and stale content leads to bad decisions.\n\n**Token budget:** 20,000 chars per file, ~150,000 chars total across all bootstrap files.\n\n## File Inventory\n\n| File | Purpose | Loaded When | Sub-agents? |\n|------|---------|-------------|-------------|\n| `AGENTS.md` | Boot sequence, checklists, behavioral rules | Every turn (all agents) | Yes |\n| `SOUL.md` | Persona, tone, values, continuity philosophy | Every turn (all agents) | Yes |\n| `TOOLS.md` | Env-specific notes (SSH, TTS, cameras, devices) | On-demand reference (part of bootstrap set) | Yes |\n| `USER.md` | Human profile, preferences, relationship context | Every turn (all agents) | Yes |\n| `IDENTITY.md` | Name, emoji, avatar, self-description | Every turn | Yes |\n| `HEARTBEAT.md` | Periodic check tasks and health routines | Every heartbeat turn | Depends |\n| `BOOT.md` | Startup actions (requires `hooks.internal.enabled`) | On gateway startup | No |\n| `BOOTSTRAP.md` | First-time onboarding script — delete after use | New workspaces only | No |\n| `MEMORY.md` | Long-term curated facts and iron-law rules | Main sessions only | No |\n| `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | Daily session logs | Loaded per AGENTS.md boot sequence | No |\n| `checklists/*.md` | Step-by-step ops guides | Referenced in AGENTS.md, loaded on demand | No |\n\n**Security rule:** MEMORY.md must NEVER be loaded in group chats or sub-agent sessions — it contains private context that should not leak.\n\nFor full details on each file's design, anti-patterns, and section structure, see [references/workspace-files.md](references/workspace-files.md).\n\n## Workspace Paths\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace/` | Default workspace for main agent |\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace-<profile>/` | Per-profile workspace (multiple agents) |\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace/vendor/OpenClaw-Memory/` | Vendor-managed base files (synced from upstream) |\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/` | Checklist files referenced from AGENTS.md |\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/` | Daily session logs |\n| `~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/` | On-demand documentation (NOT auto-loaded) |\n\nConfig key: `agents.defaults.workspace` or per-agent `agents.list[].workspace`.\n\n## Workflow: Audit Existing Workspace\n\nUse when workspace files may be bloated, stale, or redundant.\n\n1. **Read all active files** — AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, USER.md, IDENTITY.md, HEARTBEAT.md, BOOT.md, MEMORY.md\n2. **Check character counts:**\n   ```bash\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/IDENTITY.md\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n   # Or all at once:\n   wc -c ~/.openclaw/workspace/*.md\n   ```\n3. **Flag files over 10,000 chars** — prime candidates for trimming or offloading to `docs/`\n4. **Check for redundancy** — same fact in SOUL.md and AGENTS.md? Same tool note in TOOLS.md and MEMORY.md?\n5. **Check for staleness** — outdated SSH hosts, old tool names, deprecated rules, historical context that's no longer needed\n6. **Check MEMORY.md discipline** — should contain curated facts, lessons learned, decisions, and critical rules — not raw session summaries or task-specific notes\n7. **Propose targeted edits** — trim, move to docs/, or restructure\n\nSee [references/optimization-guide.md](references/optimization-guide.md) for specific optimization strategies.\n\n## Workflow: Set Up New Workspace\n\nUse when creating a workspace for a new agent from scratch.\n\n**File creation order** (matters for boot sequence to work):\n\n1. `SOUL.md` — persona and values first; everything else follows from identity\n2. `AGENTS.md` — boot sequence, safety rules, checklist table\n3. `IDENTITY.md` — name, emoji, avatar\n4. `USER.md` — human profile and preferences (main agent only)\n5. `TOOLS.md` — environment-specific notes (add as you discover env details)\n6. `MEMORY.md` — start minimal; only truly universal iron laws\n7. `HEARTBEAT.md` — periodic health checks (optional, add when needed)\n8. `BOOT.md` — startup hooks (optional, only if `hooks.internal.enabled = true`)\n9. `BOOTSTRAP.md` — first-run onboarding (optional; delete after first successful startup)\n\n**Minimal viable workspace:** AGENTS.md + SOUL.md + TOOLS.md. Everything else is optional.\n\n**BOOTSTRAP.md note:** If creating a BOOTSTRAP.md, include a self-deletion instruction at the end:\n```\n## Final Step\nDelete this file: exec `rm ~/.openclaw/workspace/BOOTSTRAP.md`\n```\n\n## Workflow: Memory Distillation\n\nUse periodically (weekly or monthly) to keep MEMORY.md lean.\n\n1. **Read all recent daily logs:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` files from the past period\n2. **Identify candidates for promotion to MEMORY.md:**\n   - Rules violated more than once (recurring mistakes)\n   - Hard-won discoveries that aren't in skills docs\n   - Env-specific facts that should always be in context (not left to memory_search recall)\n3. **Check what's already in MEMORY.md** — avoid duplicates\n4. **Draft additions** — use iron-law format: concise, action-oriented, unambiguous\n5. **Archive old daily logs** — move files older than 30 days to `memory/archive/` or delete\n6. **Check MEMORY.md total size** — keep under 10,000 chars; if larger, review for rules that are now stable enough to move to a skill's SKILL.md instead\n\n**Do NOT put in MEMORY.md:**\n- Long narratives or session summaries\n- Things already covered in skill docs\n- Anything specific to a single past task\n- Episodic or task-specific memories (store those via memory_search/SQLite instead)\n\n## Workflow: Add or Update a Checklist\n\nUse when adding a new high-risk operation type or updating an existing checklist.\n\n1. **Create or edit** `checklists/<operation-name>.md`\n2. **Structure:**\n   ```markdown\n   # Checklist: <Operation Name>\n\n   ## Pre-flight\n   - [ ] Step 1\n   - [ ] Step 2\n\n   ## Execution\n   - [ ] Step 3\n\n   ## Verification\n   - [ ] Confirm outcome\n   - [ ] Log result in memory\n   ```\n3. **Register in AGENTS.md** — add a row to the checklists table:\n   ```markdown\n   | <Operation description> | `checklists/<filename>.md` |\n   ```\n4. **Keep checklists short** — if a checklist exceeds ~50 lines, it's probably trying to be documentation; move narrative content to `docs/` and keep only the actionable steps\n\n## Workflow: Update TOOLS.md\n\nUse when adding a new tool, device, or environment capability.\n\n**TOOLS.md = environment-specific cheat sheet.** It should contain:\n- SSH hosts and common commands for this specific machine\n- TTS provider, voice IDs, and any quirks\n- Camera IDs or device names for this setup\n- Node device IDs or names\n- Any local aliases or shortcuts that aren't obvious\n\n**Do NOT put in TOOLS.md:**\n- General skill documentation (use skill SKILL.md files)\n- Things that are the same across all environments\n- Installation instructions (use docs/)\n\n**Format conventions:**\n```markdown\n# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\n## SSH\n- Main server: `ssh user@hostname`\n\n## TTS\n- Provider: Edge\n- Voice: zh-CN-XiaoxiaoNeural\n\n## Cameras\n- Living room: node-id `abc123`, device `camera-0`\n```\n\n## Common Issues\n\n### File exceeds token limit\n**Symptom:** File is over 20,000 chars; OpenClaw may truncate it.\n**Fix:** Audit for content that belongs in `docs/` (loaded on demand) instead of the bootstrap file. Move detailed references, historical context, and long examples out. Keep only what needs to be on every turn.\n\n### MEMORY.md leaking to groups\n**Symptom:** Agent shares private context in group chats or Discord.\n**Fix:** Ensure MEMORY.md boot step in AGENTS.md is gated: \"Main session only: Read MEMORY.md\". Verify the agent's boot sequence explicitly checks session type before loading.\n\n### Boot sequence not loading files\n**Symptom:** Agent doesn't know about content in SOUL.md, USER.md, or MEMORY.md at session start.\n**Fix:** Check that AGENTS.md boot sequence explicitly names each file to read. The agent won't auto-load files — it follows the boot sequence instructions in AGENTS.md. Verify `hooks.internal.enabled = true` in config if using BOOT.md.\n\n### MEMORY.md growing too large\n**Symptom:** File approaches or exceeds 10,000 chars; reading it on every turn wastes significant context.\n**Fix:** Run memory distillation workflow. Move stable rules that have been incident-free for months into relevant skill SKILL.md files. Delete rules that are no longer relevant.\n\n### Workspace changes not taking effect\n**Symptom:** Agent still uses old content after editing a workspace file.\n**Fix:** Workspace files are read at session start per the boot sequence. Restart the gateway or start a new session for changes to take effect.\n\n## Reference Files\n\n| Reference | Coverage |\n|-----------|---------|\n| [workspace-files.md](references/workspace-files.md) | Deep-dive on each file: purpose, design principles, anti-patterns, section structure |\n| [optimization-guide.md](references/optimization-guide.md) | Token efficiency strategies, audit commands, distillation process |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774498331820}}
{"type":"message","id":"77abc6ad","parentId":"66179edb","timestamp":"2026-03-26T04:12:11.845Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_EfQBcK6OOyN0te5KXiOBNviW|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b38819ba5da9f9323421bc2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ACTIVE_TASK_TEMPLATE.md\n\nStatus: active\nPriority: P1\nStarted: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\nUpdated: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\nWorkspace: /absolute/path\nOwner: main-session\nUser Trigger: original user instruction\nResume Entry: first file/report/command to reopen\n\n## Goal\n- One-sentence definition of the task to finish\n\n## Acceptance\n- Deliverable or proof 1\n- Deliverable or proof 2\n\n## Current\n- Exactly one item being executed now\n\n## Next\n- Next pending item\n- Next pending item after that\n\n## Completed\n- [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] Finished item + proof\n\n## Evidence\n- /absolute/path/to/file\n- command + key output summary\n\n## Blockers\n- None\n\n## Rules\n- `Current` must contain exactly one active item.\n- After finishing `Current`, move it to `Completed`, add proof under `Evidence`, then promote the first item in `Next` into `Current`.\n- Prefer rewriting the whole file once instead of chaining multiple partial edits.\n- After each write, read the file back and verify `Current`, `Next`, and `Completed` before reporting the new state.\n- If prompt context reports `Integrity Warnings`, repair the file before claiming the task state changed.\n- Only set `Status: blocked` when the blocker is real and specific.\n- Only set `Status: done` when `Acceptance` is met.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774498331829}}
{"type":"message","id":"19fb6dff","parentId":"77abc6ad","timestamp":"2026-03-26T04:12:11.855Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3wfhLNQZtUT0xOyn1q6ViWKI|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b40819ba3ddf8a1ba8786bc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport re\nimport sys\nimport tempfile\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nMETA_FIELDS = [\n    \"Status\",\n    \"Priority\",\n    \"Started\",\n    \"Updated\",\n    \"Workspace\",\n    \"Owner\",\n    \"User Trigger\",\n    \"Resume Entry\",\n]\n\nSECTION_FIELDS = [\n    \"Goal\",\n    \"Acceptance\",\n    \"Current\",\n    \"Next\",\n    \"Completed\",\n    \"Evidence\",\n    \"Blockers\",\n]\n\nSECTION_SET = set(SECTION_FIELDS)\nMETA_SET = set(META_FIELDS)\n\n\ndef normalize_item(value: str) -> str:\n    text = value.strip()\n    if not text:\n        return \"\"\n    return re.sub(r\"^[-*]\\s+\", \"\", text).strip()\n\n\ndef normalize_items(values: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    items = [normalize_item(value) for value in values]\n    return [item for item in items if item and item.lower() != \"none\"]\n\n\ndef parse_active_task(path: Path) -> dict[str, object]:\n    text = path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    meta = {field: \"\" for field in META_FIELDS}\n    sections = {field: [] for field in SECTION_FIELDS}\n\n    current_section: str | None = None\n    for raw_line in text.splitlines():\n        line = raw_line.rstrip()\n        heading_match = re.match(r\"^##\\s+(.+?)\\s*$\", line)\n        if heading_match:\n            name = heading_match.group(1).strip()\n            current_section = name if name in SECTION_SET else None\n            continue\n\n        label_match = re.match(r\"^([A-Za-z][A-Za-z ]+):\\s*(.*)$\", line)\n        if label_match:\n            name = label_match.group(1).strip()\n            value = label_match.group(2).strip()\n            if name in META_SET:\n                meta[name] = value\n                current_section = None\n                continue\n            if name in SECTION_SET:\n                current_section = name\n                if value:\n                    sections[name].append(value)\n                continue\n\n        if current_section in SECTION_SET:\n            stripped = line.strip()\n            if stripped:\n                sections[current_section].append(stripped)\n\n    for key in sections:\n        sections[key] = normalize_items(sections[key])\n\n    return {\"meta\": meta, \"sections\": sections}\n\n\ndef render_active_task(state: dict[str, object]) -> str:\n    meta = state[\"meta\"]\n    sections = state[\"sections\"]\n\n    lines: list[str] = []\n    for field in META_FIELDS:\n        value = str(meta.get(field, \"\")).strip()\n        if value:\n            lines.append(f\"{field}: {value}\")\n    if lines:\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    for field in SECTION_FIELDS:\n        lines.append(f\"## {field}\")\n        items = normalize_items(list(sections.get(field, [])))\n        if items:\n            lines.extend(f\"- {item}\" for item in items)\n        else:\n            lines.append(\"- None\")\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines).rstrip() + \"\\n\"\n\n\ndef atomic_write(path: Path, content: str) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(\n        \"w\",\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n        dir=path.parent,\n        delete=False,\n        prefix=f\".{path.name}.\",\n        suffix=\".tmp\",\n    ) as handle:\n        handle.write(content)\n        temp_path = Path(handle.name)\n    temp_path.replace(path)\n\n\ndef print_summary(path: Path, state: dict[str, object]) -> None:\n    meta = state[\"meta\"]\n    sections = state[\"sections\"]\n    payload = {\n        \"path\": str(path),\n        \"status\": meta.get(\"Status\", \"\"),\n        \"updated\": meta.get(\"Updated\", \"\"),\n        \"current\": sections.get(\"Current\", []),\n        \"next\": sections.get(\"Next\", []),\n        \"completed_count\": len(sections.get(\"Completed\", [])),\n        \"evidence_count\": len(sections.get(\"Evidence\", [])),\n        \"blockers\": sections.get(\"Blockers\", []),\n    }\n    print(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n\n\ndef cmd_show(args: argparse.Namespace) -> int:\n    path = Path(args.path).expanduser().resolve()\n    state = parse_active_task(path)\n    print_summary(path, state)\n    return 0\n\n\ndef cmd_advance(args: argparse.Namespace) -> int:\n    path = Path(args.path).expanduser().resolve()\n    state = parse_active_task(path)\n    meta = state[\"meta\"]\n    sections = state[\"sections\"]\n\n    current = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Current\", [])))\n    next_items = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Next\", [])))\n    completed = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Completed\", [])))\n    evidence = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Evidence\", [])))\n    blockers = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Blockers\", [])))\n\n    if args.complete_current:\n        completed.extend(current)\n        current = []\n\n    explicit_completed = normalize_items(list(args.complete or []))\n    if explicit_completed:\n        completed.extend(explicit_completed)\n        if current and any(item == current[0] for item in explicit_completed):\n            current = []\n\n    if args.append_completed:\n        completed.extend(normalize_items(list(args.append_completed)))\n\n    if args.append_evidence:\n        evidence.extend(normalize_items(list(args.append_evidence)))\n\n    if args.clear_blockers:\n        blockers = []\n    if args.set_blocker:\n        blockers = normalize_items(list(args.set_blocker))\n\n    if args.next is not None:\n        next_items = normalize_items(list(args.next))\n\n    if args.current and args.promote_next:\n        raise SystemExit(\"不能同时使用 --current 和 --promote-next\")\n\n    if args.current:\n        current = [normalize_item(args.current)]\n    elif args.promote_next:\n        if next_items:\n            current = [next_items[0]]\n            next_items = next_items[1:]\n        else:\n            current = []\n\n    if len(current) > 1:\n        raise SystemExit(\"Current 只能包含一个执行项\")\n\n    meta[\"Updated\"] = args.updated or datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\")\n    if args.status:\n        meta[\"Status\"] = args.status\n\n    sections[\"Current\"] = current\n    sections[\"Next\"] = next_items\n    sections[\"Completed\"] = completed\n    sections[\"Evidence\"] = evidence\n    sections[\"Blockers\"] = blockers\n\n    content = render_active_task(state)\n    atomic_write(path, content)\n    verified = parse_active_task(path)\n    print_summary(path, verified)\n    return 0\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n        description=\"Read and atomically update ACTIVE_TASK.md.\",\n    )\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    show_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"show\", help=\"Print ACTIVE_TASK summary.\")\n    show_parser.add_argument(\"--path\", required=True, help=\"Path to ACTIVE_TASK.md\")\n    show_parser.set_defaults(func=cmd_show)\n\n    advance_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"advance\",\n        help=\"Atomically rewrite ACTIVE_TASK current/next/completed/evidence state.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--path\", required=True, help=\"Path to ACTIVE_TASK.md\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--status\", help=\"New Status value\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--updated\", help=\"Explicit Updated timestamp\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--complete-current\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"Move existing Current item into Completed before other updates.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--complete\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Compatibility alias: append the provided item to Completed.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--current\", help=\"Set the new Current item\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--promote-next\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"Promote the first Next item into Current.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--next\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Replace Next list; repeat for multiple items.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--append-completed\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Append an item to Completed; repeat for multiple items.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--append-evidence\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Append an item to Evidence; repeat for multiple items.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--set-blocker\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Replace Blockers with the provided item(s).\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--clear-blockers\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"Clear Blockers.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.set_defaults(func=cmd_advance)\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    return int(args.func(args))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774498331845}}
{"type":"message","id":"0673cc20","parentId":"19fb6dff","timestamp":"2026-03-26T04:12:11.900Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_G6FMAWPQUGDij311QbztY6Xh|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b21b5b44819baacce7e1e243a6f6","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"path\": \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md\",\n  \"status\": \"done\",\n  \"updated\": \"2026-03-26 11:38\",\n  \"current\": [],\n  \"next\": [],\n  \"completed_count\": 3,\n  \"evidence_count\": 3,\n  \"blockers\": []\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":33,"aggregated":"{\n  \"path\": \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md\",\n  \"status\": \"done\",\n  \"updated\": \"2026-03-26 11:38\",\n  \"current\": [],\n  \"next\": [],\n  \"completed_count\": 3,\n  \"evidence_count\": 3,\n  \"blockers\": []\n}","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774498331889}}
