norGqcY6vLDpbcYMYO_LMlLbxgzu_M3A0yKKZlAi6Z8f6o2w9exkLj2Gr_BBzxWEHryzKRDZriPYoX9tePdVqBfSBVUmlqw-OiokJjGiG34vqvHb1N-40W88IAz1i8Az3i4Uqni4TbFeoLDrry1fD65geBnBXilcOzDwrl3JEtoRsYRFZihrmQHGB2-ei62ZIXBst1Sm7xrvuhba5GKiR8Jlx4oqzOnEaG-4TRopSDnhNzSbvPp8CnxzZqLAR1eXdtLvqmWpi1Ny3y75ZymY7KqaMSPO3y2lOzZkeFV8tnfSd84Fhz_PbahdYhJp7QY-PLhWOrAO4Q91hmeE2s9dhR4xcyLmo75CpRY4tzCACeBXwj3rZ2sPV_YJUzDBBcaVRcFi-QxatJ6_U2AtS8cr0t7c8wE55Zp4uJXtiyx_hcVYIGsWtzxoYHN1oPMNC84RF0fYkQ0_e4MEvBM5druBmOun8b6ZH4m_hTGlUDH33D7qwsDyba4hW6HicS8-TcTAG84cu6N2STsUv9XqWrbgYuR02U7ZVAhmP0OHtDl83RYBrF8-S-z2NDsws2oTuvwQLIgL72SFG6swyUCuqxq4cVAIzmLphRhsR3r51bbXcuVH5vR0B_5NlzrG3ChGOQGs9QJAYLMjtmNRy36jwsjIjUBpvB1GwJ_UmW8c10YpMiGeiuEf1J0zcXOFvvISr459sr-rWXiyBY7dffnfVUKmFmvEn_daH_ZoIsCBjT9c1BhCsG5ASMZYCqYAT7_2va7LeCNURX8M8I1H4b6XKLWRibgbm_exL4nhV9rpQaFU7FeTmbWOpehQ5BLEPzBsdLVbbphS7K5XlQ-JKb6-ItVbA6ohiQY5Um4xoojTkuwKJUoKonJSuDE0f89KcKnN7VF0u3NEHSHn7wfzdjR-ZPU9Ez48kwoRt71Y5sjuk=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering script implementation**\\n\\nI need to implement an actual send for validation. It seems like using Python might be better than shell for tasks related to configuration and logging. I wonder if I should rewrite the script in Python, but keep the .sh file name. \\n\\nI want to maintain started_at and finished_at status in the file to track timed tasks. Since the user mentioned fixing the schedule, maybe I could add a status file or log for that, along with a JSON state file for workout reminders. Creating an install script for crontab might also be necessary!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning a simple fix**\\n\\nThe simplest fix might be to rewrite the shell script to use openclaw message send and update a state file, possibly using inline Python or date commands. However, shell JSON handling isn’t very pretty, so I think creating a new Python script named `scripts/run_workout_reminder.py` would be a better approach, keeping the .sh file as a wrapper.\\n\\nSince the user asked for a fix, I’ll consider updating the checklist after each tool call, ensuring we focus first on the coding. Once that's done, I'll check the git status, commit changes, and manually validate the results.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating new scripts**\\n\\nI’m thinking about creating a new executable `scripts/workout_reminder.py` along with a wrapper script `scripts/workout_reminder.sh` that invokes it using Python 3. It seems the current cron jobs could reference the .py file directly. \\n\\nI should include optional flags such as `--dry-run`, `--target-user`, `--account`, and `--channel`. The default target could be set to the current user, and I’m considering making it configurable through a JSON file, possibly located in `memory/workout_reminder_config.json` or `scripts/workout_reminder_config.json`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing workout reminder scripts**\\n\\nI'm working on setting up the workout reminder configuration. I’ll create a JSON file in the workspace to handle the user's schedule while considering robustness. Maybe I'll implement a state file to keep track of when reminders start and finish. I also think it would be beneficial to incorporate logging for easier tracking. I’ll need to verify the accessibility of the default binary path under cron and write a Python script to manage the reminders efficiently.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Designing workout reminder system**\\n\\nI'm outlining the design for the workout reminder. The Python script will contain a workout plan stored in a dictionary organized by day, along with a message builder. I'll check for a configuration file to load, or default to certain settings. The script will send messages through Openclaw and log the status of each reminder. There’s also a need for a wrapper script to execute the Python code. I think I'll also create an install script for the cron job to ensure it's reusable and maintainable.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Resolving paths in scripts**\\n\\nI need to ensure I'm using the exact path for the shell commands, particularly `/Library/Frameworks` and using `/usr/bin/python3` for Python. Since the Openclaw CLI is found in the home path, the shell script will need to efficiently resolve that. I want to make sure everything's set up correctly so the scripts work seamlessly. Getting these paths right is crucial for avoiding any issues when executing the commands.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning file edits**\\n\\nI need to edit some files. I’m considering whether to use a write command for new files or an edit command for existing ones. For existing .sh files, I think rewriting with the write command might be the way to go. It's important to craft these commands carefully to avoid any mistakes! I want to ensure everything is done smoothly and correctly. Let’s be thorough with this task!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_khNAa073Z7cDMKvUH89xjRqL|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b3378c64819bb698bf11d17a05e0","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_workout_reminder.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport shutil\nimport subprocess\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nWORKSPACE = Path.home() / \".openclaw\" / \"workspace\"\nCONFIG_FILE = WORKSPACE / \"memory\" / \"workout_reminder_config.json\"\nSTATE_FILE = WORKSPACE / \"memory\" / \"workout_reminder_state.json\"\nLOG_FILE = WORKSPACE / \"logs\" / \"workout_reminder.log\"\nOPENCLAW_BIN_CANDIDATES = [\n    str(Path.home() / \".local\" / \"share\" / \"fnm\" / \"aliases\" / \"default\" / \"bin\" / \"openclaw\"),\n    shutil.which(\"openclaw\") or \"\",\n    \"openclaw\",\n]\nDEFAULT_CONFIG = {\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n    \"account\": \"feishu-assistant\",\n    \"target_user\": \"user:ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n}\n\nPLANS = {\n    1: \"周一：背部雕刻与呼吸校准\\n• 死虫式 4组×16次\\n• 单臂哑铃划船 4组×12次/侧\\n• 仰卧哑铃 Pullover 3组×12次\\n• 有氧：划船机30分钟\",\n    2: \"周二：下肢后侧日\\n• 哑铃罗马尼亚硬拉 4组×12次\\n• 负重臀桥 4组×15次\\n• 鸟狗式 3组×12次/侧\\n• 有氧：椭圆机30分钟\",\n    3: \"周三：胸肩塑形与核心\\n• 哑铃平卧推胸 4组×12次\\n• 哑铃侧平举 4组×15次\\n• 死虫式 4组×16次\\n• 有氧：划船机30分钟\",\n    4: \"周四：下肢前侧日\\n• 哑铃箱式深蹲 4组×12次\\n• 靠墙静蹲 3组×60秒\\n• 侧卧抬腿 3组×20次/侧\\n• 有氧：椭圆机30分钟\",\n    5: \"周五：全身高效代谢日\\n• 循环模式：硬拉→划船→推胸 各12次 ×4轮\\n• 有氧：划船机30分钟\",\n    6: \"周六：休息日\\n• 可以轻松散步或瑜伽拉伸\",\n    7: \"周日：休息日\\n• 建议使用筋膜枪放松全身\",\n}\n\n\ndef now_str() -> str:\n    return datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\n\n\ndef load_config() -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if not CONFIG_FILE.exists():\n        return dict(DEFAULT_CONFIG)\n    try:\n        payload = json.loads(CONFIG_FILE.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except Exception:\n        return dict(DEFAULT_CONFIG)\n    return {**DEFAULT_CONFIG, **payload}\n\n\ndef write_state(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n    STATE_FILE.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    STATE_FILE.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n\ndef resolve_openclaw_bin() -> str:\n    for candidate in OPENCLAW_BIN_CANDIDATES:\n        if candidate and Path(candidate).exists():\n            return candidate\n    for candidate in OPENCLAW_BIN_CANDIDATES:\n        if candidate:\n            return candidate\n    return \"openclaw\"\n\n\ndef run_cmd(cmd: list[str], timeout: int = 120) -> tuple[int, str, str]:\n    try:\n        proc = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=timeout)\n        return proc.returncode, proc.stdout or \"\", proc.stderr or \"\"\n    except FileNotFoundError as exc:\n        return 127, \"\", str(exc)\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired as exc:\n        return 124, exc.stdout or \"\", exc.stderr or f\"timeout after {timeout}s\"\n\n\ndef build_message(now: datetime) -> str:\n    plan = PLANS.get(now.isoweekday(), \"今日：自由活动\\n• 轻运动 + 拉伸\")\n    return (\n        f\"🧘 精英减脂增肌 - {now:%m月%d日}\\n\\n\"\n        \"⏰ 12:00-13:30 课程表\\n\\n\"\n        f\"{plan}\\n\\n\"\n        \"🥗 练后补给（14:00前）：\\n\"\n        \"• 碳水：120-150g 蒸紫薯\\n\"\n        \"• 蛋白：180g 牛肉/虾肉/鸡肉\\n\"\n        \"• 蔬菜：多样化\\n\"\n        \"• 补剂：维生素D3\\n\\n\"\n        \"⚠️ 心率红线：绝不上180，感觉不适立刻停下！\"\n    )\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"发送健身计划提醒\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--target-user\", help=\"Override target user, e.g. user:ou_xxx\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    now = datetime.now()\n    cfg = load_config()\n    if args.target_user:\n        cfg[\"target_user\"] = args.target_user\n\n    message = build_message(now)\n    started_at = now_str()\n    cmd = [\n        resolve_openclaw_bin(), \"message\", \"send\",\n        \"--channel\", str(cfg.get(\"channel\") or DEFAULT_CONFIG[\"channel\"]),\n        \"--account\", str(cfg.get(\"account\") or DEFAULT_CONFIG[\"account\"]),\n        \"--target\", str(cfg.get(\"target_user\") or DEFAULT_CONFIG[\"target_user\"]),\n        \"-m\", message,\n        \"--json\",\n    ]\n    if args.dry_run:\n        cmd.append(\"--dry-run\")\n\n    rc, out, err = run_cmd(cmd, timeout=120)\n    info = (out.strip() or err.strip())[-4000:]\n    success = rc == 0\n    status = \"DRY_RUN_OK\" if (success and args.dry_run) else \"OK\" if success else \"FAILED\"\n    state = {\n        \"started_at\": started_at,\n        \"finished_at\": now_str(),\n        \"status\": status,\n        \"date\": now.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\"),\n        \"date_tag\": now.strftime(\"%Y%m%d\"),\n        \"channel\": cfg.get(\"channel\"),\n        \"account\": cfg.get(\"account\"),\n        \"target_user\": cfg.get(\"target_user\"),\n        \"dry_run\": args.dry_run,\n        \"log_file\": str(LOG_FILE),\n        \"message_preview\": message[:200],\n        \"push\": {\n            \"ok\": success,\n            \"info\": info,\n            \"command\": cmd[:-1] if args.dry_run else cmd[:-1],\n        },\n    }\n    write_state(state)\n    print(json.dumps(state, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n    return 0 if success else 1\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    raise SystemExit(main())\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_workout_reminder.py\",\"content\":\"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\nfrom __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport argparse\\nimport json\\nimport shutil\\nimport subprocess\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\nWORKSPACE = Path.home() / \\\".openclaw\\\" / \\\"workspace\\\"\\nCONFIG_FILE = WORKSPACE / \\\"memory\\\" / \\\"workout_reminder_config.json\\\"\\nSTATE_FILE = WORKSPACE / \\\"memory\\\" / \\\"workout_reminder_state.json\\\"\\nLOG_FILE = WORKSPACE / \\\"logs\\\" / \\\"workout_reminder.log\\\"\\nOPENCLAW_BIN_CANDIDATES = [\\n    str(Path.home() / \\\".local\\\" / \\\"share\\\" / \\\"fnm\\\" / \\\"aliases\\\" / \\\"default\\\" / \\\"bin\\\" / \\\"openclaw\\\"),\\n    shutil.which(\\\"openclaw\\\") or \\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"openclaw\\\",\\n]\\nDEFAULT_CONFIG = {\\n    \\\"channel\\\": \\\"feishu\\\",\\n    \\\"account\\\": \\\"feishu-assistant\\\",\\n    \\\"target_user\\\": \\\"user:ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\\\",\\n}\\n\\nPLANS = {\\n    1: \\\"周一：背部雕刻与呼吸校准\\\\n• 死虫式 4组×16次\\\\n• 单臂哑铃划船 4组×12次/侧\\\\n• 仰卧哑铃 Pullover 3组×12次\\\\n• 有氧：划船机30分钟\\\",\\n    2: \\\"周二：下肢后侧日\\\\n• 哑铃罗马尼亚硬拉 4组×12次\\\\n• 负重臀桥 4组×15次\\\\n• 鸟狗式 3组×12次/侧\\\\n• 有氧：椭圆机30分钟\\\",\\n    3: \\\"周三：胸肩塑形与核心\\\\n• 哑铃平卧推胸 4组×12次\\\\n• 哑铃侧平举 4组×15次\\\\n• 死虫式 4组×16次\\\\n• 有氧：划船机30分钟\\\",\\n    4: \\\"周四：下肢前侧日\\\\n• 哑铃箱式深蹲 4组×12次\\\\n• 靠墙静蹲 3组×60秒\\\\n• 侧卧抬腿 3组×20次/侧\\\\n• 有氧：椭圆机30分钟\\\",\\n    5: \\\"周五：全身高效代谢日\\\\n• 循环模式：硬拉→划船→推胸 各12次 ×4轮\\\\n• 有氧：划船机30分钟\\\",\\n    6: \\\"周六：休息日\\\\n• 可以轻松散步或瑜伽拉伸\\\",\\n    7: \\\"周日：休息日\\\\n• 建议使用筋膜枪放松全身\\\",\\n}\\n\\n\\ndef now_str() -> str:\\n    return datetime.now().strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\\\")\\n\\n\\ndef load_config() -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    if not CONFIG_FILE.exists():\\n        return dict(DEFAULT_CONFIG)\\n    try:\\n        payload = json.loads(CONFIG_FILE.read_text(encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\"))\\n    except Exception:\\n        return dict(DEFAULT_CONFIG)\\n    return {**DEFAULT_CONFIG, **payload}\\n\\n\\ndef write_state(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\\n    STATE_FILE.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n    STATE_FILE.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")\\n\\n\\ndef resolve_openclaw_bin() -> str:\\n    for candidate in OPENCLAW_BIN_CANDIDATES:\\n        if candidate and Path(candidate).exists():\\n            return candidate\\n    for candidate in OPENCLAW_BIN_CANDIDATES:\\n        if candidate:\\n            return candidate\\n    return \\\"openclaw\\\"\\n\\n\\ndef run_cmd(cmd: list[str], timeout: int = 120) -> tuple[int, str, str]:\\n    try:\\n        proc = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=timeout)\\n        return proc.returncode, proc.stdout or \\\"\\\", proc.stderr or \\\"\\\"\\n    except FileNotFoundError as exc:\\n        return 127, \\\"\\\", str(exc)\\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired as exc:\\n        return 124, exc.stdout or \\\"\\\", exc.stderr or f\\\"timeout after {timeout}s\\\"\\n\\n\\ndef build_message(now: datetime) -> str:\\n    plan = PLANS.get(now.isoweekday(), \\\"今日：自由活动\\\\n• 轻运动 + 拉伸\\\")\\n    return (\\n        f\\\"🧘 精英减脂增肌 - {now:%m月%d日}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"⏰ 12:00-13:30 课程表\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        f\\\"{plan}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"🥗 练后补给（14:00前）：\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"• 碳水：120-150g 蒸紫薯\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"• 蛋白：180g 牛肉/虾肉/鸡肉\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"• 蔬菜：多样化\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"• 补剂：维生素D3\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n        \\\"⚠️ 心率红线：绝不上180，感觉不适立刻停下！\\\"\\n    )\\n\\n\\ndef main() -> int:\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\\\"发送健身计划提醒\\\")\\n    parser.add_argument(\\\"--dry-run\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n    parser.add_argument(\\\"--target-user\\\", help=\\\"Override target user, e.g. user:ou_xxx\\\")\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    now = datetime.now()\\n    cfg = load_config()\\n    if args.target_user:\\n        cfg[\\\"target_user\\\"] = args.target_user\\n\\n    message = build_message(now)\\n    started_at = now_str()\\n    cmd = [\\n        resolve_openclaw_bin(), \\\"message\\\", \\\"send\\\",\\n        \\\"--channel\\\", str(cfg.get(\\\"channel\\\") or DEFAULT_CONFIG[\\\"channel\\\"]),\\n        \\\"--account\\\", str(cfg.get(\\\"account\\\") or DEFAULT_CONFIG[\\\"account\\\"]),\\n        \\\"--target\\\", str(cfg.get(\\\"target_user\\\") or DEFAULT_CONFIG[\\\"target_user\\\"]),\\n        \\\"-m\\\", message,\\n        \\\"--json\\\",\\n    ]\\n    if args.dry_run:\\n        cmd.append(\\\"--dry-run\\\")\\n\\n    rc, out, err = run_cmd(cmd, timeout=120)\\n    info = (out.strip() or err.strip())[-4000:]\\n    success = rc == 0\\n    status = \\\"DRY_RUN_OK\\\" if (success and args.dry_run) else \\\"OK\\\" if success else \\\"FAILED\\\"\\n    state = {\\n        \\\"started_at\\\": started_at,\\n        \\\"finished_at\\\": now_str(),\\n        \\\"status\\\": status,\\n        \\\"date\\\": now.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d\\\"),\\n        \\\"date_tag\\\": now.strftime(\\\"%Y%m%d\\\"),\\n        \\\"channel\\\": cfg.get(\\\"channel\\\"),\\n        \\\"account\\\": cfg.get(\\\"account\\\"),\\n        \\\"target_user\\\": cfg.get(\\\"target_user\\\"),\\n        \\\"dry_run\\\": args.dry_run,\\n        \\\"log_file\\\": str(LOG_FILE),\\n        \\\"message_preview\\\": message[:200],\\n        \\\"push\\\": {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": success,\\n            \\\"info\\\": info,\\n            \\\"command\\\": cmd[:-1] if args.dry_run else cmd[:-1],\\n        },\\n    }\\n    write_state(state)\\n    print(json.dumps(state, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\\n    return 0 if success else 1\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    raise SystemExit(main())\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4f4qgAjyBV9WXb1shf90uTOe|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b3378c74819bbe34b2c8d5070181","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/workout_reminder.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\"\nexec /usr/bin/python3 \"$WORKSPACE/scripts/run_workout_reminder.py\" \"$@\"\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/workout_reminder.sh\",\"content\":\"#!/bin/bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\n\\nWORKSPACE=\\\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\\\"\\nexec /usr/bin/python3 \\\"$WORKSPACE/scripts/run_workout_reminder.py\\\" \\\"$@\\\"\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_iNCLoi5yuHJqGYVPqZkLKIuu|fc_0142f9a21f5351e00169c4b3378c7c819ba253181563567f92","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/install_workout_reminder_cron.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nWORKSPACE=\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\"\nLOG_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/logs\"\nRUN_SCRIPT=\"$WORKSPACE/scripts/workout_reminder.sh\"\nMARKER=\"# WORKOUT_REMINDER_1130\"\nCRON_LINE=\"30 11 * * 1-5 cd $WORKSPACE && /bin/bash $RUN_SCRIPT >> $LOG_DIR/workout_reminder.log 2>&1 $MARKER\"\n\nmkdir -p \"$LOG_DIR\"\nTMP_FILE=\"$(mktemp)\"\ncrontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"$MARKER\" > \"$TMP_FILE\" || true\nprintf '%s\\n' \"$CRON_LINE\" >> \"$TMP_FILE\"\ncrontab \"$TMP_FILE\"\nrm -f \"$TMP_FILE\"\n\necho \"Installed: $CRON_LINE\"\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/install_workout_reminder_cron.sh\",\"content\":\"#!/bin/bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\n\\nWORKSPACE=\\\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\\\"\\nLOG_DIR=\\\"$WORKSPACE/logs\\\"\\nRUN_SCRIPT=\\\"$WORKSPACE/scripts/workout_reminder.sh\\\"\\nMARKER=\\\"# WORKOUT_REMINDER_1130\\\"\\nCRON_LINE=\\\"30 11 * * 1-5 cd $WORKSPACE && /bin/bash $RUN_SCRIPT >> $LOG_DIR/workout_reminder.log 2>&1 $MARKER\\\"\\n\\nmkdir -p \\\"$LOG_DIR\\\"\\nTMP_FILE=\\\"$(mktem