{"type":"message","id":"1c71eb9e","parentId":"1c6b1062","timestamp":"2026-03-26T13:26:46.708Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Organizing citation details**\n\nI need to consider whether to include line citations for relevant files like tester_scheduled_guard_latest.md and run_tester_scheduled_guard.py. It’s probably best to mention file paths, while keeping things straightforward for the user. I should also explain why the warning \"一直发策略守卫警告\" is a recurring issue due to crontab scheduling and a stale index. There were also more serious warnings on 3/25, indicating a halt state not being properly inherited.\n\n**Clarifying guard warnings**\n\nThe guard's function is working as intended. As of 3/26, critical warnings disappeared, leaving only stale CSV issues, which suggests the guard has effectively reduced severity. One warning in the evening reports indicates precheck is at FULL_HALT, with the data health off-hours guarded, leading to a downgrade for protection. There are two \"guard\" types causing alerts. I can explain that the logs reflect the latter due to different scheduled tasks reporting the same state. It's not a sign of new problems each time.\n\n**Suggesting alert improvements**\n\nI think it would be a good idea to suggest some improvements for the alert system. Specifically, I should consider deduplicating alerts so that users only receive notifications on status changes or critical issues. This way, we can reduce the noise in the reports and make it easier for everyone to focus on the really important updates. Keeping alerts relevant and targeted could really enhance the user experience!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0142f9a21f5351e00169c53401e36c819b9df33b532b9ebd10\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpxTQVgHP0qVanf3gNHjiIOx9_IYjrvvt7RiaAMpvouWVf_MsHLem0Bqoy71DCS_9UpSpiq4hymW8e8e5nAZfu5_mJfe-eaRBgxHm-RfDqpD2cSOVE36k1xVSJFUT7nKXaUpV8v-pbb2txL5oHCtBx4lhKSGUtsRvqiyRq9VCQmEF4DlDwyTeARD